76561197994180829,Recommended,285050,10236313,"Posted: 25 May, 2014",all,accent,"I was just randomly looking for some cheap small games when I ran into this and it seemed interesting enough to give a try. It actually manages to be quite fun even though it looks rather unpolished and has a few bugs. The game mechanics remind me a bit of Game Dev Tycoon, it's the same kind of ""click through lots of options and wait for your product to finish and see how well it did"" stuff, except in this one it's much easier to do well, at least for me. Even if it is too easy, it's still fun to see your films do well and get awards. The bugs and sometimes weird user interface might put some people off, but it seems that the developer is actively updating the game and fixing bugs, so it will get better. I would really expect a more polished audiovisual presentation nowadays though, even from small indie developers. Still definately worth a try if movies and tycoon games interest you."
