76561198022948546,Recommended,285050,10373824,"Posted: 6 June, 2014",all,DaBlue,"Does anyone remember that game, ""The Movies"" by Lionhead?  Basic idea was you created a film studio from the ground up, and ran every aspect about it from the screenwriting, acting, and release.  It was pretty much a god game only instead of workign with people, you work with movies.  This game tries to do the same thing, with mixed results.  On one hand, having everything mainly be text based, makes it easy (for the most part) on your machine, but leaves what models there are, less appealing.  However, there is a big issue with this game, which is why I do not recommend it.  Around the time of this game's release I was rather harsh.I still stand by the notion that, at release, the game was broken, and barely working.  However, credit does go out to the developer, for working with the community to help resolve the bigger issues in a timely manner, and now a days the game works pretty well.  Granted, we then get into that grey area of a broken game getting released and fixed later.  However, once again, with those issues resolved we can get into the meat of the game itself.Being mostly text based, the game looks alright, with really the big issue being the placeholder models used for actors, producers, and directors.  It might be more of a personal taste, but I would have perferred no models than what is used.Even though the game becomes rather tedious after a while, that does give the player a bigger freedom to try and experiment, but with limited results.  Either dump all your money into a project, and because one thing was right it'll make every dime back, or fail miserably still makes the game difficult to fully recommend.  Yet, at the end of the day, it's a cheap simulator game, for a subject area not many games do, and isn't trying to boost its bugs as part of the game, so...plus there.  There is content in this game, and for a film buff, it's hard to not try and enjoy at least.It's more of a quick burst kind of game.  Not to expense, you load it up--which being mostly text based does make the game load and run smoothly when it works--and play for about an hour."
